That line is correct, but it’s not enough.  A JTextField’s ActionListener is invoked when the user presses Enter in that JTextField.  If the user never presses Enter, the ActionListener is never called.

You can force it to be called by using [InputVerifier](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/19/docs/api/java.desktop/javax/swing/InputVerifier.html):

    SetAction setAction = new SetAction(row, col, temp, board);
    temp.addActionListener(setAction);

    temp.setInputVerifier(new InputVerifier() {
        @Override
        public boolean verify(JComponent component) {
            setAction.actionPerformed(null);
            return true;
        }
    });

